        <p>Mobile and wireless technologies provide an ever-increasing number of opportunities for companies and individuals worldwide. However, there are unique challenges associated with this type of communication, including network latency, data throughput, security, location, and backhaul and last-mile connectivity.</p>

        <p>Mobile network infrastructure is based on a software-defined architecture with separation between data and control planes. Such separation allows the service provider to utilize the mobile network infrastructure and build innovative mobile network applications and services. This network architecture allows a flexible provisioning and deployment model, optimizing the infrastructure utilization.</p>

